with special items. Of course, players will need to choose their faction before beginning to rumble.\r\n\r\nIn addition to general exploration, the game offers flight once players reach a certain level. It also features daily events, and plenty of social activities. These include house building, farming, and marriage, among other things.\r\n','MMORPG','Windows','Anisage Games','Anisage Games','2022-08-01','Windows 7 or higher','Pentium 4, Dual Core','2 GB RAM','Nvidia 7600 or equivalents','3 GB'),(98,531,'Magic Spellslingers','Magic Spellslingers is the latest entry based on Witzards of the Coast’s popular card game Magic: The Gathering.','Magic Spellslingers is the latest entry based on Witzards of the Coast’s popular card game Magic: The Gathering. Developed by Pipeworks Studios and Seismic Games, this card battler is intended to be an entry point into the Magic universe. Like other games of the same genre players will start out choosing a hero. In this case they choose from a selection fo Spellslingers, each offering unique abilities and strategies as well as cards to use in battle.\r\n\r\nNot only is Magic Spellslingers a unique card game in its own right, it’s also intended to be an introduction to the Magic universe. Players can take on challenges designed for both first-time layers and experienced veterans anywhere they’re at. Even more, they have the option to create teams and share resources and decks with friends, and work together on strategies. Of course, teammates can compete against each other as well.','Card Game','Windows','Wizards of the Coast LLC','Pipeworks Studios, Seismic Games','2022-08-05','Windows 10','Intel Core i5-4460 @ 3.20 GHz','8 GB','GeForce GTX 560','12 GB'),(99,533,'A.V.A Global','A.V.A is a free-to-play online first-person shooter with multiple game modes, unique customizations, as well as PvP and PvE gameplay.','A.V.A is a free-to-play online first-person shooter with multiple game modes, unique customizations, as well as PvP and PvE gameplay.\r\n\r\nIf you are worried about running out of different game modes, customization and maps have no fear, in A.V.A there more than 14 maps, several game modes including Annihilation, Demolition and Breach! Plus the weapon attachment system allows you to modify your own weapons. Pick your favorite class and jump into the action!\r\n\r\n','Shooter','Windows','NEOWIZ','NEOWIZ','2022-08-24','Windows7 64Bit','Intel Core 2 Quad Q6600 /AMD Phenom 9500','4 GB RAM','NVIDIA GeForce 9600 GT / ATI Radeon HD 4850 (512 MB)','30 GB'),(100,534,'Lost Light','A post-apocalyptic shooter built around creating a realistic experience.','Shooter fans looking for a game built around creating a realistic experience will want to give NetEase Games’ Lost Light a look. Set in a post-apocalyptic environment, the game features lots of interesting places modeled to be like real-world locations to explore. It also boasts weapons intended to provide the most realistic experience possible. Each has up to 12 modifiable parts and hundreds of optional components.\r\n\r\nDespite the massive armory, the focus of Lost Light isn’t necessarily to run and gun. The game is survival, and that means making it to the evacuation point. If that means avoiding combat and just snagging loot along the way, that’s the way to go. Players can choose to go with a partner or to go it alone. But survival is often easier when you have someone to help you along.\r\n<p>Those who survive will be able to stash their loot and begin work on building a base of operations. That even means setting up a shop for trading with other players in the game.\r\n\r\nLost Light is available on mobile devices and PC. The latter can be downloaded directly or via Steam. The game offers cross-platform features as well.','Shooter','Windows','NetEase Games','NetEase Games','2022-08-04','Windows7SP1, Windows8.1, Windows10','intel i3 530','4 GB RAM','GTS450','10 GB available space'),(101,524,'Temperia: Soul of Majestic','Fans of collectible card games, are you looking for something a bit different from the normal fare? Then a peek at Moonwolf Entertainment and A2 Softworks’ Temperia: Soul of Majestic might be in order.','Fans of collectible card games, are you looking for something a bit different from the normal fare? Then a peek at Moonwolf Entertainment and A2 Softworks’ Temperia: Soul of Majestic might be in order. The strategy card game uses an open-handed game style where all cards are face up and combines two decks into one. The decks are made up of 20 Creature and 20 Equipment cards.\r\n\r\nThe game is designed to focus on player skill rather than the luck of the draw and takes inspiration from chess where everything is on display. Good players will be able to use this to their advantage when determining strategies. \r\n\r\nThe game limits randomness and its impact on the game. Time and again, players will need to prove their skills in order to climb the leaderboard.','Card Game','Windows','Leonardo Interactive','MoonWolf Entertainment, A2 Softworks','2022-07-26','Windows 8','64-compatible, duo core, 2.5GHz or better','8000 MB RAM','HD graphics 620','1 GB'),(102,525,'MultiVersus','The Warner Bros lineup meets Smash in Player First Games’ MultiVersus.','The Warner Bros lineup meets Smash in Player First Games’ MultiVersus, a platform fighter featuring a wide range of characters from Warner’s movies, cartoons, and more. Fight Batman as Shaggy. Team up with Steven Universe and Finn. Make use of their unique abilities and take your opponents down.\r\n\r\nThe game features a large roster from popular media and shows as well as maps based on locations found there. That means players can visit the Batcave or Jake and Finn’s Treefort among other places. And they\'ll do it while taking par tin epic 1v1, 2v2, or 4 players free for all battles. \r\n\r\nThere’s also a handy training mode where players can hone their skills. The game is available on all platforms and includes cross-platform play and progression.','Fighting','Windows','Warner Bros. Games','Player First Games','2022-07-19',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(103,532,'World of Runes','An adorable anime-style MMO featuring cute pets and collectable cards.','World of Runes is an adorable anime-style MMO featuring cute pets. Players can choose between four different playable classes to explore the game’s world with. To help players get started, the game begins with a series of Novice Quests as an introduction to all the necessary systems. That includes the game’s controls. It also offers players a bit of a boost with more XP and rewards than regular quests.\r\n\r\nThe four available classes in the game are the Swordsman, Archer, Mage, and Cleric. Each features three abilities and is reliant upon each other in battle. The Swordsman fills both the physical melee and tank roles. Archer fills the physical long-range support and offers burst and high hit. Mage is your obvious magical DPS – both long-range and sustained. And Cleric is mostly support but with magical melee and sustained DPS.\r\n\r\nAnother feature of the game is the collectible cards, an MVP system that players can use to collect rare items. These include equipment, cards, and other items. These can be sold for Crystals in the game’s Exchange. Finally, players can collect pets to use in battle. Stats on pets vary depending on a few factors.','MMORPG','Web Browser','F5 Game Company Limited','R2 Games','2022-06-13',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(104,550,'Goose, Goose, DUCK','A social deduction game with geese.','Goose, goose, DUCK is a social deduction game developed and published by Gaggle Studios, Inc. Slightly parodying the children’s game Duck, duck, goose; Goose, goose, DUCK puts players in the roles of geese trying to complete a mission. However, there are duck spies in their midst trying to stop them.\r\n\r\nAs with other social deduction games, it’s up to the geese to discover who the infiltrators are while managing to complete their mission. The ducks will do as all infiltrators do, including taking out the geese one at a time, in order to sabotage the mission.\r\n\r\nGoose, goose, DUCK features public and private lobbies, built-in proximity voice chat, seven playable maps, five different modes, and a whole bunch of optional sub-roles. The game is available to play for free via Steam.','Strategy','Windows','Gaggle Studios, Inc.','Gaggle Studios, Inc.','2021-10-03','Windows 7','Intel Core2 Duo 2.4ghz+','2 GB','Integrated Graphics','400 MB'),(105,513,'Super Squad','Prepare yourself. It’s time for Mayhem. Super Squad is a multi-player online shoot-’em-up (or MOSH)!','Prepare yourself. It’s time for Mayhem. And you’ll get that from Bad Fox Studios’ Super Squad, a multi-player online shoot-’em-up (or MOSH). It combines the playstyle of MOBA’s with the tactics of RTSs.\r\n\r\nThe game features a wide roster of characters including soldiers, goat men, angels, vikings, pirates, dogs, and even something called a “Florp”. The characters fill basic team roles – damage, support, etc, so players will need to choose wisely in order to build the best team and destroy the competition. Also take into account the various combat styles of each character, and their preferred weapons. These abilities range from being able to burrow under enemies and blow them up with landmines to grappling  your way around the map and picking your foes off from a distance.\r\n\r\nBattle your way across a military base. Fight on Mars. Or even take down a mothership. There are several maps to choose from, with more on the way. ','MOBA','Windows','Bad Fox Studios','Bad Fox Studios','2021-06-25','Windows 7/8.1/10','2.6 GHz Dual Core','4 GB RAM','Nvidia GTX 460 or equivalent','16 GB available space'),(106,512,'Sherwood Extreme','High action arcade shooter Sherwood Extreme sends players on a mission to save the kingdom!','Cage Studio’s high action arcade shooter Sherwood Extreme sends players on a mission to save the kingdom in the most extreme way possible. Parkour. Maneuver your way through battle. Flip off turrets, swing through trees, make your way up, over and around mountains, and do it all while destroying your enemies, swinging over them and popping off headshots – if you’re good enough, that is.\r\n\r\nSherwood Extreme is available to play in both single-player and co-op, with it becoming even more crazy when friends team up. Complete challenges together. Collect loot. Discover the secrets of Sherwood. And do it all in the most ridiculous way possible.\r\n\r\nIf crazy fun with your friends isn’t enough because you’re a bit more competitive, there’s a full leader board as well with a variety of challenges to take on. Test your speed and precision and parkour your way to the top.','Shooter','Windows','CAGE Studios','CAGE Studios','2021-05-12','Windows 7','Dual core 2.0 GHz','4 GB RAM','Intel HD 520','1 GB available space'),(107,509,'Smash Legends','Classic fairy tales get wild with 5minlab and LINE Games Corporation’s brawl-action game Smash Legends.','Classic fairy tales get wild with 5minlab and LINE Games Corporation’s combat action game Smash Legends. Take a trip to the Library World and play as one of several legends based on classic fairy tale characters like Peter Pan, Red Riding Hood, Puss in Boots, and even the Ugly Duckling.\r\n\r\nWhile a more casual game, designed for cross-play on mobile devices and PC, Smash Legends includes a variety of modes ranging from 1v1 duel to a mini, 8-player battle royale mode. Other modes include a 3v3 area capture, 3v3 team deathmatch, a 4 player harvest mode, and more. The game also offers several maps to play on, all on an island floating above the clouds.\r\n\r\nSo, pick your favorite fairy tale character and beat up your friends in friendly, fun combat. The game will offer new modes in the future, so there will always be something fun to do.\r\n','Fighting','Windows','LINE Games Corporation','5minlab','2021-04-13','WINDOWS® 7, 8, 8.1, 10 (64Bit)','Intel Dual co